#! <SUBDOCUMENTS>
#! <SUBDOCUMENT
#!   NAME="PointCloudLASClassifier"
#!   ARCGIS_COMPATIBILITY=""
#!   CATEGORY="Point Clouds"
#!   DESCRIPTION="&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;The transformer uses _classification attribute for outputting each class through its own port. It also sets _classification_description attribute, which contains the explanation of the class assigned to a point cloud.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;The transformer does not split the cloud, it only helps separate point clouds after splitting and easily identify the content of each class.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;br/&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;The classification values are assigned based on the standard ASPRS classification values:&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&#10;    &lt;br/&gt;&#10;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;0 - Created, never classified&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;1 - Unclassified&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;2 - Ground&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;3 - Low Vegetation&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;4 - Medium Vegetation&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;5 - High Vegetation&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;6 - Building&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;7 - Low Point (Noise)&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;8 - Model Key point (Mass Point)&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;9 - Water&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;10 - Reserved for ASPRS Definition&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;11 - Reserved fro ASPRS Definition&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;12 - Overlap Points&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;13-31 - Reserved for ASPRS Definition &lt;/p&gt;&#10;"
#!   DOC_DYNAMIC_INPUT_ATTRS="0"
#!   DOC_EXTENTS="2390.38 1716"
